{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17518116","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17518116"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:00:41+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:00:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12878"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12878","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12878"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.01,0.51,0.12,0.26]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5320"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84889"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5320","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5320"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12878"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"69168"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"32"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"194"},{"type":"tags","id":"1493"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11627"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"9046"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9175"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13863"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28884"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42828"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44881"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84889","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/84889"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old woman is retrieved from the site of a car accident in which she was a restrained front seat passenger. During the primary survey onsite, she had multiple lacerations and contusions on her head. She had a patent airway and was haemodynamically stable with a GCS score of 13 (E4, V4, M5). An intravenous catheter has been inserted in the dorsum of her right hand.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUpon arrival at the emergency department, C-spine immobilisation is commenced. Primary survey reveals:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAirway: slightly obstructed but improves with jaw thrust\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBreathing: RR 12, SpO2 94% on RA, equal air entry bilaterally\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECirculation: BP 160/80 mmHg, HR 60/min, CCRT \u0026lt;2 seconds\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDisability: opens her eyes only to a trapezius squeeze. She is able to make incoherent sounds, and moves into a decorticate posture with pain stimulus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the immediate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Insertion of large bore cannulas","Cardiopulmonary resuscitation","Endotracheal intubation","Insert laryngeal mask airway","Urgent non-contrast CT brain scan"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has deteriorated rapidly, and her GCS has reduced significantly. She has a current GCS score of 7: eye opening 2, verbal response 2, motor response 3. This clinical picture is consistent with a worsening intracranial trauma with early suggestion of raised intracranial pressure (systolic BP 160 mmHg and HR 60/min), therefore the priority must be to protect the airway. A GCS of \u0026lt;8 in the trauma setting demands prompt \u003Cstrong\u003Eendotracheal intubation\u003C/strong\u003E because of the substantial risk of loss of airway reflexes and aspiration.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst\u003Cstrong\u003E cardiopulmonary resuscitation \u003C/strong\u003Emay be needed the airway must first be protected and then\u003Cstrong\u003E large bore cannulas\u003C/strong\u003E can be inserted. This is clearly described in the ALS algorithm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInsertion of laryngeal mask airway\u003C/strong\u003E will not prevent aspiration of regurgitated fluids, which is a risk in low GCS trauma patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerform urgent non-contrast CT brain scan\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as airway protecting is a much higher priority. This may be the next step in management once the patient has been stabilised.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Endotracheal intubation is indicated when patients have a GCS\u003C8 in a trauma setting.","An acute drop in GCS in trauma setting warrants prompt action. In this case - airway protection."],"references":["https://aci.health.nsw.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0011/195167/NSW-Health-ITIM-Emergency-airway-management-trauma-patient-summary.pdf","Langeron O, Birenbaum A, Amour J. Airway management in trauma. Minerva Anestesiol. 2009 May;75(5):307-11. PMID: 19412149.","https://www.europeantraumacourse.com/on-line-resources","https://vle.rcseng.ac.uk/course/view.php?id=548\u0026section=3"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"69168"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12878"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"69168","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/69168"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-12T17:06:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-12T17:06:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5320"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84889"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,